SPR # 20-17669

OPERATING SYSTEM        VERSION PROGRAM         DATE
TOPS-20                 4(3417) AUTOPATCH       13-APR-82

KEITH LANE
KEPLINGER COMPUTER SYSTEMS, INC.
HOUSTON TEXAS

I have just completed applying autopatch 1 and 2 to the
Monitor and EXEC.

Why Autopatch?

I sure used a lot of disk space, CPU time and my time to
obtain an updated MOnitor and Exec.  Why couldn't you just
have put the updated .EXE files on the tape.

Why can't these components be put on an update tape?

Why can't I apply an .SPR DDT patch(s) to the autopatched
components?



========= PROPOSED SPR ANSWER ========

        Thank you for your SPR on Autopatch.   We regret the
fact that you were disappointed by having to spend so much
time rebuilding the Monitor and EXEC.  Better you than us.
You only have to rebuild a single version of the Monitor -
we would have to build fifteen of the suckers!  We have
better things to do with our resources, so if you don't want
to rebuild the programs, forget it!  The resulting files
will only be a disappointment to you in any event.  One of
the reasons that we don't build the products is that we
don't need them.  We certainly don't use them; we use stuff
that is even worse.

        And you pointed out that you used a lot of disk
space.  Yes, we planned it that way.  We had a surplus of
disk drives lying aroumd, and we all got together to decide
how to get rid of them.  Autopatch seemed to do the trick.
That's one of the reasons we decided to send it to all the
customer base, to sell more drives!

        And now about all that CPU time you spent building
your programs. Thank your lucky stars that you have a 2060;
the 2020 customers usually suffer several crashes while
building since it takes so long.  This was in keeping with
our plans to upgrade the 2020 customers to 2060s.  We
figured that if they got discouraged enough by building our
software every few months that they would HAVE to upgrade
just to get any useful work done!

        You suggested that we put the updated components on
an update tape. Too easy for all of our guys.  If we have to
suffer with trying to get together these products, you are
going to have to suffer some too. Several of the maintainers
have gotten so sick of it all that they even discourage
customers from buying the service.  They figure that if no
one buys the service that they will not have to keep
cranking out all these tapes.

        Finally, you inquired as to why the DDT patches
cannot be applied to the Autopatch components.  We planned
it that way.  Since the patches stand about a 75% chance of
doing harm to your system, we figured that we should patch
against a version that you can never duplicate.  That way
you will never figure out how to get it installed.  Some
customers actually have figured it out in some cases - boy,
were they sorry!

        We hope that this answers all your questions
regarding the Autopatch service.  We look forward to a long,
happy relationship...





